We will replace the `sorry` in the `lindenbaum` theorem with the appropriate witness and proof term.

The goal is to prove `โU : Set (Formula โ), U = construction_omega T hT โง U โ (L : Set (Formula โ)) โ U โ (L : Set (Formula โ))`.
We provide the witness `U = construction_omega T hT`.
The proof term should be `fun _ => trivial`, because the statement becomes `(U = construction_omega T hT โง U โ (L : Set (Formula โ))) โ U โ (L : Set (Formula โ))`, which simplifies to `True` (as `U โ (L : Set (Formula โ))` is the same as `U โ (L : Set (Formula โ))`).

```tactics
theorem lindenbaum : โU : Set (Formula โ), U = construction_omega T hT โง U โ (L : Set (Formula โ)) โ U โ (L : Set (Formula โ)) := by 
  use construction_omega T hT
  intro h
  tauto
```

The `use construction_omega T hT` tactic provides the witness for the existential quantifier. The goal then becomes `(construction_omega T hT = construction_omega T hT โง construction_omega T hT โ (L : Set (Formula โ))) โ construction_omega T hT โ (L : Set (Formula โ))`.
The hypothesis `h` is `(construction_omega T hT = construction_omega T hT โง construction_omega T hT โ (L : Set (Formula โ)))`.
The goal is `construction_omega T hT โ (L : Set (Formula โ))`.
This is precisely what `h` asserts, so `tauto` can close the goal. Alternatively, `exact h.2` would also work.

The complete code with the replacement is:
